-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cnf1707818817811.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cnf1707818817811.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cnf1707818817811.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ocb1665702556016\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Arithmetic Operators\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__arithmetic_operators_49113\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Arithmetic operators take numerical values as operands and return a single numerical value.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__p_d14639e1_d14640e1_d14641e1\">The following expressions use arithmetic operators:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">23 + 24 ; = 47\n8 + 7 * 6\n(1 + vTax/100) * vAmount</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__p_d14642e1_d14643e1_d14644e1\">Arithmetic operators have a lower priority than access operation and a higher priority than relational and logical operators. The arithmetic operators themselves are subdivided into two levels of priority. Within their own subdivision, they are evaluated from left to right.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Arithmetic Operators</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__1\">\n Operator\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__3\">\n Priority\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">*</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__2\">\n Multiplication\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"3\">\n 1\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__2\">\n Division\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">%</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__2\">\n Modulo\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">+</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__2\">\n Addition\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"2\">\n 2\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">-</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1__entry__2\">\n Subtraction\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__topic_d10827e1_d10828e1_d10829e1_d10830e1_d10831e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d924264e162\">\n                        \n Modulus Operator\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__p_d14648e1_d14649e1_d14650e1\">The value of <var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">%</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Y</var> is computed with the absolute values of <var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var> and <var class=\"keyword varname\">Y</var>. The sign of the result is the same as the sign of X. Example results of modulus calculations are shown in the table:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Results of modulus calculations</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__1\">\n Value of X\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__2\">\n Value of Y\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__3\">\n Result of X%Y\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__1\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__2\">\n 3\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__3\">\n 1\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__1\">\n -1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__2\">\n 3\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__3\">\n -1\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__1\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__2\">\n -3\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__3\">\n 1\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__1\">\n -1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__2\">\n -3\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ocb1665702556016__table_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1__entry__3\">\n -1\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__topic_d10832e1_d10833e1_d10834e1_d10835e1_d10836e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d924264e267\">\n                        \n Rounding\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ocb1665702556016__p_d14654e1_d14655e1_d14656e1\">Uniface arithmetic expressions use string representations of the numbers as input, and return a string representation of the result, truncated at 38 digits. If the 39th digit is <code class=\"ph codeph\">5</code> or higher, the number is rounded upwards.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6105579\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6105579\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Arithmetic Operators Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Arithmetic Operators Arithmetic operators take numerical values as operands and return a single numerical value. The following expressions use arithmetic operators: 23 + 24 ; = 47 8 + 7 * 6 (1 + vTax/100) * vAmount Copy Arithmetic operators have a lower priority than access operation and a higher priority than relational and logical operators. The arithmetic operators themselves are subdivided into two levels of priority. Within their own subdivision, they are evaluated from left to right. Table 1. Arithmetic Operators Operator Description Priority * Multiplication 1 / Division % Modulo + Addition 2 - Subtraction Modulus Operator The value of X % Y is computed with the absolute values of X and Y . The sign of the result is the same as the sign of X. Example results of modulus calculations are shown in the table: Table 2. Results of modulus calculations Value of X Value of Y Result of X%Y 1 3 1 -1 3 -1 1 -3 1 -1 -3 -1 Rounding Uniface arithmetic expressions use string representations of the numbers as input, and return a string representation of the result, truncated at 38 digits. If the 39th digit is 5 or higher, the number is rounded upwards. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}